title: McGraw Hill - Schaum's Outlines Statistics (4th Ed - 2008).pdf
description:
From Amazon:


The guides that help students study faster, learn better-and get top grades

Updated to match the latest developments in the field of statistics, this new edition includes dozens of new problems showing output from EXCEL, SAS, SPSS, STATISTIX, and MINITAB, all of which are in general use for in college courses on statistics.


From the Back Cover

Chapters include: Variables and Graphs * Frequency Distributions * The Mean, Median, Mode, and Other Measures of Central Tendency * The Standard Deviation and Other Measures of Dispersion * Moments, Skewness, and Kurtosis * Elementary Probability Theory * The Binomial, Normal, and Poisson Distributions * Elementary Sampling Theory * Statistical Estimation Theory * Statistical Decision Theory * Small Sampling Theory * The Chi-Square Test * Curve Fitting and the Method of Least Squares * Correlation Theory * Multiple Regression * Analysis of Variance * Nonparametric Tests * Analysis of Time Series * Statistical Process Control and Process Capability
